                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Hyderabad Dec. 13: Telugu Desam Party chief N. Chandrababu Naidu was set to spend the night at a police station following his arrest this afternoon after a sit-in near the Andhra Assembly.          
	The former chief minister, who was protesting against government inaction on farmers travails after the recent havoc caused by rain, was later taken to Gosha Mahal police station with his party MLAs. Earlier, Naidu and other party MLAs were prevented from escorting farmers representatives into the Assembly premises.          
	We will go directly to the Assembly along with farmers representatives from the police station itself and try to raise their issues in the Assembly, Naidu told reporters at the police station.                  
	 Allahabad (PTI): Allahabad High Court on Monday granted bail to former Uttar Pradesh chief secretary Neera Yadav and industrialist Ashok Chaturvedi. The two were sentenced to four years imprisonment in a Noida land scam case last week. Justice Vinod Prasad passed the order on the bail petitions of Yadav and Chaturvedi. The CBI special court had convicted the duo on charges of corruption.                  
	Thiruvananthapuram (PTI): Congress veteran and former Kerala chief minister K. Karunakaran has been put on ventilator support in a city hospital after his condition deteriorated. Karunakaran had been admitted to the hospital on Saturday with chest and urinary infections.                                                                                                                                              
